    The Class Range represents a Generable range of integers.

    The Class RangeGenerator is used to produce the numbers.
    Zip<O>
    The Class Zip joins more lists toghether in this way: (1, 2, 3) zip (4, 5, 6) -> ((1, 4), (2, 5), (3, 6))
    ZipLongest<O>
    The Class ZipLongest does the same as zip but also for non-equally-sized iterables.
